Here's the SVG code to recreate the vertical color bars design shown in the image (280 x 280 px):


This SVG creates five vertical bars:
1. A maroon/dark red bar on the left
2. A black transition bar
3. A green bar in the middle
4. Another black transition bar
5. A white/light bar on the right

Each color has a width of 70px, while the black transition bars are 35px wide, totaling 280px in width. The height is also 280px as specified.

Here's the SVG code to recreate the horizontal gradient design shown in the image:

```svg
<svg width="280" height="280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Background gradient -->
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="backgroundGradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="0%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#ff3300" /> <!-- Red-orange at top -->
      <stop offset="15%" stop-color="#ff0066" /> <!-- Pink-red -->
      <stop offset="30%" stop-color="#9933ff" /> <!-- Purple -->
      <stop offset="45%" stop-color="#33cccc" /> <!-- Teal -->
      <stop offset="60%" stop-color="#ffffff" /> <!-- White -->
      <stop offset="75%" stop-color="#cccccc" /> <!-- Light gray -->
      <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#666666" /> <!-- Dark gray at bottom -->
    </linearGradient>
  </defs>
  
  <!-- Rectangle with gradient fill -->
  <rect width="280" height="280" fill="url(#backgroundGradient)" />
</svg>
```

This SVG creates a 280×280 pixel image with a vertical gradient that transitions through the colors visible in your image: starting with a red-orange at the top, then moving through pink/purple, teal, white, and finally ending with gray tones at the bottom.

I'll create SVG code to recreate this 280 x 280 px design with the green gradient at the top, a thin bright green horizontal line in the middle, and a pink/magenta gradient at the bottom:

```svg
<svg width="280" height="280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Green gradient at the top -->
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="greenGradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="0%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#4CAF50" />
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#A5D6A7" />
    </linearGradient>
    
    <!-- Pink/magenta gradient at the bottom -->
    <linearGradient id="pinkGradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="0%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#E91E63" />
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#F48FB1" />
    </linearGradient>
  </defs>
  
  <!-- Background -->
  <rect width="280" height="280" fill="white" />
  
  <!-- Top green gradient section -->
  <rect width="280" height="180" fill="url(#greenGradient)" />
  
  <!-- Middle bright green line -->
  <rect width="280" height="5" y="180" fill="#4CAF50" />
  
  <!-- Bottom pink/magenta gradient section -->
  <rect width="280" height="95" y="185" fill="url(#pinkGradient)" />
</svg>
```

This SVG creates a 280x280 pixel image with:
1. A green gradient that transitions from darker green at the top to lighter green
2. A thin bright green horizontal line in the middle
3. A pink/magenta gradient at the bottom portion

You can adjust the colors and proportions as needed to match the exact design you're trying to recreate.

```svg

    </linearGradient>

  <!-- Sky section (top 60% of image) -->
  <rect x="0" y="0" width="280" height="168" fill="url(#skyGradient)" />
```

This SVG creates a 280x280 pixel image with two main sections:
1. The top section (approximately 60% of the height) with a gradient that transitions from light blue to purple/pink and back to light blue
2. The bottom section (approximately 40% of the height) with a solid brown color

You can adjust the gradient colors and stop positions to fine-tune the appearance if needed.

Here's the SVG code to recreate the design with the colorful diagonal gradient:

```svg
      <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#9932CC" /> <!-- Purple -->
      <stop offset="25%" stop-color="#FFD700" /> <!-- Gold/Yellow -->
      <stop offset="50%" stop-color="#00CED1" /> <!-- Turquoise -->

  </defs>
  
  <rect width="280" height="280" fill="url(#diagonalGradient)" />
</svg>
```

This SVG creates a 280×280 pixel square with a diagonal gradient that transitions through purple, gold/yellow, turquoise, teal, and light cyan colors, matching the color scheme in the image. The gradient flows from the top-left to the bottom-right corner of the square.
